docs.abstract: Jerome H. Powell is a pragmatist, and one who is quietly insulating an embattled Federal Reserve often in President Trump’s cross hairs.
docs.snippet: Jerome H. Powell is a pragmatist, and one who is quietly insulating an embattled Federal Reserve often in President Trump’s cross hairs.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Jerome H. Powell has spent much of his life toiling quietly behind the scenes, first as an investment banker and later as a governor at the Federal Reserve. Even as the central bank’s chair, and arguably the global economy’s most important figure, he has maintained a low-key image.

headline.main: How the Fed Chairman Is Shielding It From Trump
headline.print_headline: Chosen, Then Demonized, by Trump, Chair Quietly Insulates Fed
